						<summary>

						<p>Inner <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the Mantrapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 18.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription may be assigned on palaeographical considerations to c. 13th century.</p>						

						<p>It states that a <hi rend="italic">daṇḍanāyaka</hi> (name not known) granted the lands as <hi rend="italic">iṟaiyili</hi> and confirmed that the worship and services are to be continued to the deity Uḍaiyār Tiruvuśāttāṉam-uḍaiya-ṉāyaṉār. Further it is known that a stipulation has been made to the effect that capital in terms of paddy should not be received (collected) from the <hi rend="italic">dēvadāṉa</hi> lands granted as <hi rend="italic">iṟaiyili</hi> from the eighteenth year. The imprecatory portion is somewhat interesting in this record.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
